headlines.description: Elijah Minnie scored 16 of his 22 points in a close first half and Eastern Michigan used a big run in the second half to roll to a 58-41 win over Ball State on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Minnie leads E Michigan to 58-41 win over Ball State

headlines.description: Zane Najdawi scored 28 points, grabbed 10 rebounds and Frankie Johnson drove for one layup to force overtime and another to give The Citadel the lead for good in the extra period on Saturday and the Bulldogs defeated Furman 100-92 to cap an intense...
headlines.shortLinkText: Najdawi, The Citadel knock off Furman 100-92 in overtime

headlines.description: Bryson Scott scored 25 points and John Konchar added 18 and Fort Wayne defeated Denver 91-63 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Scott, Konchar lead Fort Wayne to 91-63 win over Denver

headlines.description: Scottie James scored 26 points and grabbed nine rebounds and Liberty notched its third-straight win, downing Longwood 67-55 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: James leads with 26 points as Liberty downs Longwood 67-55

headlines.description: Junior Robinson made four 3-pointers and scored 20 on Saturday and Mount St. Mary's beat St. Francis (Pa.) 59-56 to move alone into second in the Northeast Conference.
headlines.shortLinkText: Robinson, Mount St. Mary's beat St. Francis (Pa.) 59-56

headlines.description: Drew Urquhart scored 18 points, Payton Henson and Trae Bell-Haynes added 16 each as hot-shooting Vermont beat UMBC 81-53 in the debut of the Retrievers' new Event Center on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Vermont spoils UMBC's debut of new arena 81-53

headlines.description: Joseph Kilgore scored nine of his 11 points in the second half as Texas A&M-Corpus Christi got off to a slow start before rallying in the second period for a 56-51 win over Incarnate Word on Saturday afternoon for its fourth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Texas A&M-CC rallies for 4th straight win, beating UIW 56-51

headlines.description: James Scott hit 5 3-pointers and totaled 30 points as Kennesaw State picked up its second win over USC Upstate in eight days, this time posting a 93-69 rout in the Atlantic Sun Conference rematch on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kennesaw State finishes sweep of USC Upstate, 93-69

headlines.description: Ahmad Thomas scored 19 of his 24 points in the second half when UNC Asheville pulled away for a 75-61 victory over Presbyterian on Saturday and took sole possession of first place in the Big South.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thomas misses triple-double by an assist in Asheville's win

headlines.description: Zjori Bosha scored 18 points with 10 rebounds and two steals and Lamar clobbered Stephen F. Austin 76-54 on Saturday to break a 10-game losing streak to the Lumberjacks, dating back to 2012.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lamar takes out 10 games of frustration on SFA, 76-54

headlines.description: Griffin Kinney scored 17 points with seven rebounds and Appalachian State upended Texas State 59-56 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kinney leads with 17, Appalachian St. upends Texas St. 59-56

headlines.description: Devin Mitchell scored a career-high 38 points to lead Georgia State to its ninth straight Sun Belt Conference victory, an 81-51 thrashing of Little Rock on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mitchell has career-high 38, Ga. State thrashes Little Rock

headlines.description: Zach Johnson and Brandon Goodwin combined for 49 points and Florida Golf Coast pulled away from Jacksonville State for an 80-55 win on Saturday night, running the Eagles' winning streak to 11, their longest at the Division I level.
headlines.shortLinkText: Johnson, Goodwin put FGCU in control of A-Sun with 80-55 win

headlines.description: Steven Whitley scored a career-high 20 points with seven assists, Nic Thomas also scored 20 points, and Norfolk State beat Morgan State 76-65 on Saturday to win its third straight.
headlines.shortLinkText: Whitley, Thomas lead Norfolk State to 76-65 win

headlines.description: Joe Cremo scored a career-high 31 points and Albany pulled away late in the second half to beat New Hampshire 83-74 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cremo scores 31 points, Albany beats New Hampshire 83-74

headlines.description: Ja Morant scored 18 points, Jonathan Stark had 17 and Murray State used a late run to pull away from UT Martin 66-53 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray State uses late surge to put away 66-53 victory

headlines.description: Jahaad Proctor had 20 points, seven rebounds and five assists on Saturday night and High Point pulled away in the middle of the second half for a 67-56 win over Campbell.
headlines.shortLinkText: High Point uses 2nd-half run to get past Campbell 67-56

headlines.description: Mike Amius had his second career double-double and Devin Peterson made five 3-pointers and finished with 25 points, both career highs, on Saturday night to help Western Carolina beat Samford 88-71.
headlines.shortLinkText: Amius, Peterson lead W. Carolina past Samford, 88-71

headlines.description: Jerrick Harding scored 29 points and Dusty Baker added 17, including a career-high tying five 3-pointers, to help Weber State beat Northern Arizona 87-55 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harding hits 5 3s, scores 29; Weber St. beats N. Arizona

headlines.description: Tommy Rutherford scored 17 points on 7-of-9 shooting and Evan Leonard had 14 points, six rebounds, seven assists and two steals on Saturday night to help UC Irvine beat Cal State Fullerton 63-58.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rutherford, Leonard lead UC Irvine past CS Fullerton, 63-58

headlines.description: Perrion Callandret had 23 points on 10-of-14 shooting and Idaho led the entire way in an 81-58 victory over Sacramento State on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Idaho beats Sacramento State 81-58

nowFeed.headline: Under Sean Miller Deandre Ayton is maximizing his enormous potential. Ayton has always possessed the physical tools and a solid basketball IQ. He has worked hard at Zona along with making the adjustments to college basketball. For a freshman big man it's really hard to dominate right away. Since he arrived in the states he was a top ranked player in his class. Would have been top 5 in last years NBA draft. Now he will be a top 3 pick and will be much more prepared.

nowFeed.headline: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.

The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.

nowFeed.headline: Houston upsets No. 5 Cincinnati 67-62, ending the Bearcats nation-leading 16-game winning streak. It's the first time the Cougars have beaten two top-10 opponents in a season since 1984.

nowFeed.headline: Ironically, Cincinnati's loss to Houston also finally gives Cincinnati its first win over a likely NCAA Tournament team.
